@startuml 15_D2_Diagnosis_Flow
!theme plain

skinparam backgroundColor #F5F7FA
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam Padding 5
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.5

skinparam title {
  FontSize 17
  FontStyle bold
  FontColor #1A237E
  BackgroundColor #E8EAF6
  BorderColor #3F51B5
  BorderThickness 2
}

skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #455A64
  ActorBorderColor #263238
  LifeLineBorderColor #B0BEC5
  ParticipantBorderColor #90A4AE
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BoxBorderColor #CFD8DC
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF8E1
  BorderColor #FFB300
  FontColor #4E342E
  FontSize 10
  BorderThickness 1.5
}

title <b>3D Data Quality Framework  \u00b7  D2 Diagnosis Engine</b>\n<size:12>Drift Classifier \u2192 Lineage Tracer \u2192 Segment Slicer \u2192 Evidence Retriever \u2192 Playbook Compiler \u2192 Prescription Router</size>

participant "D1 Anomaly\nHandover"           as D1
participant "Drift\nClassifier"              as DC
participant "Lineage\nTracer"                as LT
participant "Segment\nSlicer"                as SS
participant "Evidence\nRetriever"            as ER
participant "Playbook\nCompiler"             as PC
participant "Prescription\nRouter"           as PR
database    "DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\n(Delta)" as AnomalyDB
database    "table_daily_metrics\n(Delta)"    as MetricsDB
database    "data_catalog\n(Unity Catalog)"   as Catalog
database    "playbook_store\n(UC Volume)"     as PlaybookDB
database    "check_execution_log\n(Delta)"    as ExecLog
database    "diagnosis_evidence_log\n(Delta)" as EvidenceDB
participant "Job Run Logs\n(Jobs API 2.1)"   as JobLogs
participant "DESCRIBE HISTORY\n(Delta log)"  as DeltaHist
participant "Runbooks\n(Confluence + UC Vol)" as Runbooks
participant "GitHub Repo\n(pipeline code)"   as GitRepo
participant "ITSM Tickets\n(prior incidents)" as ITSM
participant "D3 Deflection\nEngine"          as D3
participant "Notification\nDispatcher"       as Notify

== [D2-0] Anomaly Handover from D1 ==

D1 -> AnomalyDB : Anomaly record ingested\nSELECT top-N undiagnosed anomalies\nWHERE diagnosis_status = 'PENDING'
activate D1
AnomalyDB --> D1 : {anomaly_id, rule_id, table_name,\n column_name, violation_pct,\n severity, z_score, detected_at}
deactivate D1

D1 -> DC : Trigger diagnosis pipeline\n{anomaly_id, violation_context}
activate DC

== [D2-1] Drift Classifier -- Map Anomaly to Failure Category ==

note right of DC
  Classifies anomaly into a Data Failure category:
  \u2022 VOLUME_DROP     -- row count below expected band
  \u2022 SCHEMA_CHANGE   -- column type / name changed
  \u2022 FRESHNESS_DRIFT -- data not updated on schedule
  \u2022 DISTRIBUTION_SHIFT -- statistical dist. changed
  \u2022 REFERENTIAL_BREAK -- FK / join key missing
  \u2022 CUSTOM_SQL_FAIL -- user-defined assertion failed
  \u2022 NULL_SPIKE       -- null rate > threshold
  \u2022 OUTLIER_SURGE    -- Z-score > 3\u03c3 cluster
  Classification uses rule_type + violation metadata
  (rule-based mapping; no ML required).
end note

DC -> MetricsDB  : SELECT baseline_mean, baseline_stddev,\n       last_7d_avg, last_30d_avg\nFROM   table_daily_metrics\nWHERE  table_name = ? AND column_name = ?
MetricsDB --> DC : Historical baseline stats

DC -> ExecLog    : SELECT COUNT(*), fail_reason, error_code\nFROM   check_execution_log\nWHERE  rule_id = ? AND run_date > NOW() - 7 DAYS
ExecLog --> DC   : Recent execution pattern

DC --> DC : Map failure_category + severity_band\n(CRITICAL | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW)

DC -> AnomalyDB  : UPDATE DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\nSET failure_category = ?,\n    severity_band = ?,\n    diagnosis_status = 'CLASSIFYING'

== [D2-2] Lineage Tracer -- Identify Root Table & Impact Blast Radius ==

DC -> LT : Handover: {table_name, failure_category}
deactivate DC
activate LT

note right of LT
  Traverses Unity Catalog lineage graph:
  \u2022 Upstream  -- find source tables that feed this table
  \u2022 Downstream -- find all tables / reports / jobs
                  consuming this table
  \u2022 Identifies "Patient Zero": first table in the
    upstream chain that shows the same anomaly pattern.
  Uses UC LINEAGE_EVENTS API.
end note

LT -> Catalog : GET /api/2.0/lineage-tracking/\n       table-lineage?table_name={fqn}&\n       direction=UPSTREAM&depth=5
Catalog --> LT : upstream_tables[], source_jobs[]

LT -> Catalog : GET /api/2.0/lineage-tracking/\n       table-lineage?table_name={fqn}&\n       direction=DOWNSTREAM&depth=5
Catalog --> LT : downstream_tables[], downstream_dashboards[]

LT -> MetricsDB : Cross-check upstream tables for\nsame anomaly pattern in last 48h\nSELECT table_name, violation_pct, detected_at
MetricsDB --> LT : upstream_anomalies[]

LT --> LT : Score upstream tables by anomaly\ncorrelation -> identify Patient Zero

LT -> AnomalyDB : UPDATE: blast_radius_json = {\n  patient_zero: {table, anomaly_type, detected_at},\n  upstream_affected: [...],\n  downstream_affected: [...],\n  estimated_jobs_impacted: N\n}

== [D2-3] Segment Slicer -- Isolate Exact Micro-Segment ==

LT -> SS : Handover: {table_name, failure_category, blast_radius}
deactivate LT
activate SS

note right of SS
  Slices data along known dimension columns to
  isolate which subset drives the anomaly.
  Dimension priority order (per domain config):
    Trading:    market, brand, channel, season
    DTC:        market, platform (app/web), OS, device
    CRM/adiC:   market, membership_tier, acquisition_src
    Payments:   market, payment_method, currency
  Uses Chi-square test for categorical dimensions.
  Uses Mann-Whitney U for numerical dimensions.
end note

SS -> MetricsDB  : SELECT dimension columns for table\nFROM domain_dimension_config\nWHERE domain = ? AND table_name = ?
MetricsDB --> SS : priority_dimensions[]

SS -> MetricsDB  : SELECT {dimension}, COUNT(*), violation_pct\nFROM   table_daily_metrics\nWHERE  table_name = ? AND metric_date = TODAY()\nGROUP  BY {dimension}
MetricsDB --> SS : dimension_breakdown[]

SS --> SS : Run statistical significance test\nper dimension slice\n\u2192 rank by chi-square / Mann-Whitney p-value

SS -> AnomalyDB  : UPDATE: micro_segment = {\n  dimension: 'market',\n  value: 'DE',\n  violation_lift: 3.2,\n  confidence: 0.97,\n  sample_size: 142000\n}

== [D2-4] Evidence Retriever -- Gather Diagnostic Evidence for Prescription ==

SS -> ER : Handover: {failure_category, patient_zero, micro_segment}
deactivate SS
activate ER

note right of ER
  Collects real-world evidence from 5 sources so the
  Playbook Compiler can build a grounded prescription:
  1. Job run logs    -- stderr/stdout + error stack of the
                        pipeline that last wrote the table
  2. DESCRIBE HISTORY -- recent Delta operations (WRITE / MERGE /
                        DELETE / OPTIMIZE / schema change) + operator
  3. Runbooks        -- Confluence pages + UC Volume /runbooks/
                        matching failure_category + domain
  4. GitHub codebase -- transform source that produces the table
                        (locate likely offending logic / commits)
  5. ITSM tickets    -- prior resolved incidents, same
                        failure_category + table -> reuse resolution
  Each hit is relevance-scored; low-confidence sources dropped.
end note

ER -> JobLogs   : GET /api/2.1/jobs/runs/get-output\n?run_id={source_job_run}
JobLogs --> ER  : error_trace, exit_code, log_tail

ER -> DeltaHist : DESCRIBE HISTORY {table_fqn} LIMIT 20
DeltaHist --> ER : recent_operations[], operator, commit_ts

ER -> Runbooks  : Search Confluence + UC Volume /runbooks/\nWHERE category = failure_category AND domain = ?
Runbooks --> ER : matched_runbook_refs[]

ER -> GitRepo   : Code search: table_fqn + transform name\n(recent commits touching this pipeline)
GitRepo --> ER  : candidate_source_files[], recent_commits[]

ER -> ITSM      : Search prior incidents\nWHERE failure_category = ? AND table = ? AND status = RESOLVED
ITSM --> ER     : similar_incidents[], past_resolutions[]

ER --> ER : Score + rank evidence\n-> build evidence_bundle

ER -> EvidenceDB : INSERT diagnosis_evidence_log\n{anomaly_id, job_log_ref, delta_history,\n runbook_refs, code_refs, similar_incidents,\n evidence_score, gathered_at}

ER -> AnomalyDB : UPDATE: evidence_summary_json = {...},\n              diagnosis_status = 'EVIDENCE_GATHERED'

== [D2-5] Playbook Compiler -- Build Reproducible Remediation Plan ==

ER -> PC : Handover: {failure_category, patient_zero,\n           micro_segment, evidence_bundle}
deactivate ER
activate PC

note right of PC
  Looks up matching playbook template in UC Volume:
  /Volumes/{catalog}/playbooks/{failure_category}.json
  Each playbook template contains:
  \u2022 remediation_steps[]   -- ordered action list
  \u2022 escalation_path       -- who to notify per severity
  \u2022 auto_fix_eligible      -- boolean + conditions
  \u2022 rollback_procedure     -- how to reverse the fix
  \u2022 sla_target_hours       -- expected resolution time
  \u2022 evidence_required[]    -- what to capture for audit
  Template is GROUNDED by the evidence_bundle from D2-4
  (job logs, Delta history, runbooks, code refs, prior ITSM fix).
  Playbooks are versioned (JSON, stored in UC Volume).
  Maintained by Data Governance + domain Tech Leads.
end note

PC -> PlaybookDB : LOAD playbook template\n/playbooks/{failure_category}.json
PlaybookDB --> PC : playbook_template

PC --> PC : Instantiate template with:\n  patient_zero, micro_segment, blast_radius,\n  evidence_bundle, submitter context\n\u2192 concrete prescription JSON

PC -> AnomalyDB : UPDATE: prescription = {\n  playbook_id: 'PB-NULL-001',\n  playbook_version: '2.1',\n  steps: [...],\n  auto_fix_eligible: true,\n  estimated_resolution_hours: 4,\n  sla_target: NOW() + 4h,\n  evidence_bundle: [...]\n}

== [D2-6] Prescription Router -- Route to D3 Deflection ==

PC -> PR : Handover: {prescription, severity_band, auto_fix_eligible}
deactivate PC
activate PR

PR --> PR : Route decision:\n  CRITICAL + auto_fix -> D3 Circuit Breaker\n  HIGH + auto_fix     -> D3 Domain Executor\n  ANY + manual_fix    -> D3 Approval Gate\n  LOW                 -> Notify owner only

alt CRITICAL or HIGH -- auto-fix eligible

  PR -> D3 : Dispatch prescription to D3 Deflection Engine\n{prescription, priority, domain_executor_target}
  note right of PR: Anomaly enters D3 immediately.\nSLA clock starts for resolution.

else Manual fix required

  PR -> Notify : Alert rule owner + Tech Lead\n(Email + Jira with prescription link)
  note right of PR: Owner opens prescription in Genie.\nManual remediation steps guided by playbook.

else LOW severity

  PR -> Notify : Informational alert to owner only\n(Email digest, no Jira)

end

PR -> AnomalyDB : UPDATE: diagnosis_status = 'DIAGNOSED',\n              routed_to = 'D3_DEFLECTION | MANUAL | NOTIFY',\n              diagnosed_at = NOW()

deactivate PR

== [D2 Output Summary] ==

note over D1, D3
  D2 Diagnosis produces a fully-enriched anomaly record in DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES:
  +-----------------------------------------------------------------+
  | failure_category   : DISTRIBUTION_SHIFT                         |
  | severity_band      : HIGH                                       |
  | patient_zero       : bronze.fact_orders (upstream)              |
  | blast_radius       : 4 downstream tables, 2 dashboards          |
  | micro_segment      : market=DE, platform=app (97% confidence)   |
  | evidence_bundle    : job-log + Delta history + runbook + code   |
  |                      ref + 2 prior ITSM fixes (evidence_score)   |
  | prescription       : PB-DIST-003 v1.4 (auto-fix eligible)       |
  | diagnosis_status   : DIAGNOSED                                  |
  | routed_to          : D3_DEFLECTION                              |
  +-----------------------------------------------------------------+
  Evidence is persisted in diagnosis_evidence_log for audit + reuse.
end note

@enduml
